{"title": "Death by Flashback", "content": "Basically, if a character experiences an extended flashback sequence, often explaining his origins and, especially, getting rid of all the loose ends in his Back Story, there is a good chance that he is going to be Killed Off for Real. If this is combined with gloomy omens, such as cracking pottery or falling flower petals, he is almost certainly done for.\n\nA subtrope of A Death in the Limelight. Somewhat related to My Life Flashed Before My Eyes, Really Dead Montage, except it happens before the character's death. Can be part of a Sympathetic Murder Backstory. See also How We Got Here, Retirony and Fatal Family Photo.\n\nAs a Death Trope, all Spoilers will be unmarked ahead. Beware.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathByFlashback", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CowboyBebop", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/JoJosBizarreAdventure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/EdenItsAnEndlessWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Trigun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Madlax", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaStrikers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Pokemon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Psychopass", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/MagicalGirlRaisingProject", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ThePromisedNeverland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/JuniTaisenZodiacWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Frankenstein", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDresdenFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AmericanBeauty", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Ladder49", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MenaceIISociety", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Lost", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Angel", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderDragonKnight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Supernatural", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/OnceUponATime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheVampireDiaries", "/pmwiki/